social_posts.post_text: Getting ready to #cruisenorwegian…but first we have to get there. Flight leaves in 30 minutes!!! @jetblue
Had a great day in San Juan! Hit the beach, dinner with some good friends, and ended off the night with some live music and arcade. Now…off to #CruiseNorwegian!

All aboard! Got settled in, toured the spa, had an incredible dinner at Cagney’s, Cooper had a ton of ice cream, and won $150 at the casino! Great day!!! Doing one day at sea, then hello Aruba! #cruisenorwegian #norwegianepic

We love the beaches and shore excursions…but at sea days are just as much fun! Cooper’s all about the water slides, while Ashley suns on the deck. Another great day on #NorwegianEpic! See you tomorrow Aruba! #CruiseNorwegian

Aruba was amazing! Spent the day at Eagle Beach. Went tubing before we left. Cooper kept telling the guy to go faster…I was hanging on for dear life! Then back to #NorwegianEpic for some dinner and a show. Cooper always makes us get late night crepes at The Garden Cafe — I’m not complaining! Off to Curaçao! #CruiseNorwegian

Something I really love about cruising is that we get to stop at a bunch of different beautiful places rather than just flying to one. Today, Curaçao! Spent the day with our good friends @cholewascott and @judyc428. Went snorkeling on a beautiful beach, did some shopping in town, then back to the ship for a show and dinner at Moderno — So. Much. Meat!! #CruiseNorwegian #NorwegianEpic

For almost my entire life, the only trip my dad ever talked about is when he went scuba diving in Bonaire. Never thought I’d be able to see what he was talking about…today we did, and it was beautiful! After an incredible in-room breakfast on #NorwegianEpic (and a quick stop at the on-board @starbucks), we hit the beach, went snorkeling, and took a ride on a catamaran. Back for a late lunch, a bit of hot tubbing, dinner at Shanghai, and wrapped the night at the arcade. Full day tomorrow in St. Lucia! #CruiseNorwegian

Great to be traveling on #NorwegianEpic with friends! While in #StLucia, Ashley and I went to Rodney Beach, while @cholewascott and @judyc428 took Cooper to the volcanic mud baths! One of them left it on their face for dinner at #Teppanyaki…it was quite the conversation starter! #CruiseNorwegian

Our last day aboard #NorwegianEpic, and it truly was, in every sense of the word! Today, we spent one of our favorite days in #StKitts. After an amazing breakfast on board, Ashley and I hiked to the top of Souffa Stone Mountain. Incredible views! Cooper is not quite the hiker…so our friends Scott & Judy took her on a scenic train ride around the island. Finished off the day with an incredible dinner at Le Bistro…where Cooper tried escargot! (She made me pay her $20 to do it…but so worth it!) Now back to Puerto Rico for a trip through the rain forrest before we return home. #CruiseNorwegian
This. This is what happens when Cooper insists on bringing home cupfuls of sand from every beach we went to for her friends. Do I have to tip him? #TSA
Not going to do some cheesy caption here, even though @andrewpug really wants it bad! @niallhoran here today! Super nice guy, and his new song #Heaven is out now!
Some pre- @sza dinner at @carminesnyc! Hi @chefglennrolnick!

It’s #NationalCerealDay! And on our @cerealkillerspc podcast, we celebrate by trying the second of 2 new Disney Cereals from Post. Tastes like Fruity Pebbles! Then a cereal @zScottyB brought back from Puerto Rico, and our listener Matt sent us a bunch of cheapo Amish store cereals, and we’ll try one from Malt-O-Meal.
Fun way to spend a cruddy day…lunch with the girls at @johnspizzeriaoftimessquare 🍕 and a preview performance of @badcinderellabway! Might have to buy Cooper the “Bad” hoodie 👿
Definitely pretty cool to step out of the building and be so close to this! Happy #StPatricksDay! ☘️

It's not a milestone anniversary, but it's rare to spend 28 years of your life at one job, especially one that you love so much! I've been very lucky to meet some really cool people over the years here at @z100newyork's @elvisduranshow, and to work with so many people who have become family. Here are a few pics from my archives from the very first show I worked at @northwelljbt in 1995, to just a few weeks ago in our new studios at @iheartradio in Midtown.
